Packages that should be changed/reviewed (Windows compatibility gaps)
1) macOS-only app/tooling entries in Brewfile
   - cask "ghostty"      -> recommend Windows Terminal or WezTerm
   - brew "dockutil"     -> no Windows equivalent needed (remove from Windows parity scope)
   - cask "rectangle"    -> recommend Microsoft.PowerToys (FancyZones)
   - cask "wispr-flow"   -> recommend Microsoft.PowerToys Advanced Paste/Voice alternatives

2) package format/version pins that are not portable as-is
   - brew "icu4c@77"     -> avoid strict macOS formula pin for Windows parity; use runtime-managed dependency where needed

3) likely-missing Windows parity packages to add to Wingetfile
   - bat, duckdb, fd, fzf, jq, lazygit, ripgrep, yq, zoxide
   - sevenzip, uv, graphviz, plantuml
   - kubectl, k9s, minikube, tilt
   - ffmpeg, imagemagick, poppler
   - google-chrome, obsidian, slack

4) specialized libraries from Brewfile that should not be enforced via Wingetfile unless explicitly required
   - glib, harfbuzz, librsvg, open-mpi, utf8proc, zstd, openssl@3
   - Recommendation: keep these platform-specific or install only as transitive deps of the tools that require them.

Notes
- This log is a repository-level validation record requested for Windows support review.
- Before finalizing Wingetfile updates, run validation on a Windows host:
  - winget show <PACKAGE_ID>
  - winget install --id <PACKAGE_ID> --exact
